div.div: Click the AltServer icon in the Mac menu bar, go to “Install AltStore”, then choose your device

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe center; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 202px; height: 1px; padding-top: 1390px; margin-left: 34px;
box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0; text-align: center; color: #000000;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #ffffff; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

div.div: Enter your Apple ID email address and password. This will allow AltServer to authenticate with Apple and configure your account to support sideloading apps

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-end; justify-content: unsafe flex-start; width: 142px; height: 1px; padding-top: 1499px; margin-left: 30px;
box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0; text-align: left; color: #000000;
display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #ffffff; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;
div.div: You can create a new Apple ID just for the AltStore in iOS Mail settings

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe center; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 202px; height: 1px; padding-top: 1590px; margin-left: 34px;
box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0; text-align: center; color: #000000;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #ffffff; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

div.div: Wait a few seconds, then an AltServer notification should appear on your Mac saying AltStore has been successfully installed onto your device

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe center; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 202px; height: 1px; padding-top: 1790px; margin-left: 34px;
box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0; text-align: center; color: #000000;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #ffffff; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

div.div: On your iOS device, go to Settings -> General -> Profiles & Device Management. Tap “Trust [Your Apple ID],” then tap “Trust” again to confirm

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-end; justify-content: unsafe flex-start; width: 142px; height: 1px; padding-top: 1699px; margin-left: 30px;
box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0; text-align: left; color: #000000;
display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #ffffff; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

div.div: You may need to restart your device to make AltStore appear on your Home Screen.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe center; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 216px; height: 1px; padding-top: 1930px; margin-left: 27px;
box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0; text-align: center; color: #000000;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #ffffff; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

div.div: To use AltStore on iOS 16 or later, you need to enable Developer Mode on your device by going to Settings -> Privacy and Security -> Developer Mode

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe center; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 216px; height: 1px; padding-top: 2070px; margin-left: 27px;
box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0; text-align: center; color: #000000;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #ffffff; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

div.div: Now you can install and refresh your apps in "My apps" tab, clicking "+" on top or adding repositories in Sources tab
